name: Shaker & Company
owner_biography:
Founder and Managing Director of Shaker UK Limited. 
Adam set up Shaker UK as part of a BA and MSc in Business Management coupled with his bartending exploits throughout Europe. With 15 years of experience throughout the bar industry Adam Freeth has developed Shaker into being one of the authorities on training and bartending. 
Having tended bar for the rich and famous, Freeth has also appeared on TV as an authority on drinks and appeared in national and trade press. 

Author of Professional Bartending, published in 2009 by New Holland Publishers and sold globally, with a 2nd edition.

Adam is responsible for the development and strategy of Shaker Bars Limited, Shaker UK Limited and oversees developments of the Shaker Group.

MD of Shaker Bars Limited - opened Shaker&Company October 2011. Shaker&Company brings a very fine slice of the deep south Americana, some heart and soul serving up New Orleans inspired cocktails and drinks created by some of the world's top mixologists

name: Sketch
owner_biography: A recognizable figure in France for celebrated restaurants such as Au Bascou and 404 in Paris. Mourad Mazouz opened Momo restaurant in London in 1997, winning 'Bar of the Year' in the Evening Standard for its clever mix of world music, chic staff and sexy interiors. In 2006 Mourad opened Almaz by Momo in Dubai, a superb amalgamation of modernist North African design and food. Mourad teamed up with the Prada Foundation in 2008 to open the Double Club. A Congolese 'pop-up' restaurant and bar, designed by world renowned artist Carsten Holler. Another Paris opening soon followed with the opening of Derriere. With a talent to combine the most unusual in the most unexpected way. Mourad has also published The Momo Cook Book and founded the record label Mo'Zik...

name: Mews Cocktail & Lounge Bar
owner_biography:
James Robson is a successful investor and entrepreneur having established an impressive portfolio of exclusive venues in London's most desirable locations.

After spending five years working in finance, James took an early interest in the world of hospitality and became a bartender at 190 Queens Gate. After eight years learning the trade and accumulating an enviable black book of contacts, James left to pursue the dream of pioneering his own business.

Mayfair Pizza Co was launched in 2013, after James took over the former Rocket Mayfair site and turned it into his own 120-cover pizza restaurant.

Today, James' extensive portfolio consists of four brands, five leases, nine trading areas and over one hundred employees, only closing one day of the year across the entire portfolio. 

Despite being surrounded by London's finest food and drink, James is also passionate about healthy living. As dedicated to fitness as he is to business, James has completed over twenty five marathons.

name: The Admiralty
owner_biography:
Beer has been brewed on Fuller's historic Griffin Brewery site in Chiswick since the seventeenth century.
Fuller's is well known as the brewer of London Pride and other award-winning ales such as Chiswick Bitter, ESB and 1845. Its beers are exported to about 70 countries around the world. Fuller's owns and operates over 380 pubs, inns and hotels across the south of England, with over 180 managed pubs and hotels, and over 200 tenanted pubs.

name: Jim And Tonic
address:
Mercao Metropolitano
42 Newington Causeway
London SE1 6DR
owner_biography: After starting to swap my regular post football beer for a G&T, the lads coined the nickname 'Jim And Tonic'. An idea and a concept was born! I purchased and converted our first van, 'Genevieve' and quickly saw some traction with corporate clients and wedding organisers who were desperate for an exciting and unique mobile gin bar to wow their guests/customers. Fast forward two years and we now operate three vans, as well have a permanent base at Mercato Metropolitano in London, where our bar and distillery is situated. All of the J&T crew love Gin, and it seems as if the whole country does too! It's an incredible drink and allows for so much variety and unique tweaks to flavours and tastes. Get in touch to see how we can cater for your event, or pop in and see us at our bar in Mercato Metropolitano, SE1 6DR!

name: The London Cocktail Club
owner_biography: The winners of the third series of BBC Two's 'The Restaurant', JJ Goodman and James Hopkins, have opened their new high street cocktail bar and kitchen, The London Cocktail Club, on Goodge Street.  The boys have been mentored throughout by world renowned restaurateur, Raymond Blanc OBE, and his fellow judges from the successful series, David Moore and Sarah Willingham.  According to Raymond, JJ and James won this opportunity because "from day one of the competition, they stood out from the crowd thanks to their enthusiasm and strong work ethic.  Some viewers disagreed with our choice of winner, but inside both boys is a strong business understanding.  They work together as the most outstanding team and their sense of fun is infectious."

name: The Chipping Forecast
owner_biography:
Here at The Chipping Forecast we've searched the caves and coves of Cornwall in order to find fisherman using traditional techniques to land the finest, sustainably caught fish our waters can offer. Each delivery of fish we receive, can be traced back to the boat and to the fisherman who landed the catch (many of whom are pictured on our restaurant walls).
We guarantee from hook to plate within 48 hours!

name: The Table
owner_biography:
Hi I'm the co-owner of The Table, my partners are some of the architects from the architectural practise next door, Allies and Morrison. I've been involved with food for over 18 years now, and been here for seven years. My first job was commis chef at L'Odeon on Regents Street under Head Chef Bruno Loubet with his sous chef, Anthony Dimitri. 

I've travelled the world with my profession and am deeply proud and committed to this wonderful business of food. The Table is in my heart and soul, the very floor boards tell my story. I'd love you to come round and say hi so I can tell you more about our lovely little local restaurant. I can be found here most days of the week, just ask for Shaun.
I can be contacted any time via email too; shaun@thetablecafe.com if you have any comments or queries.

name: Terry’s Cafe
owner_biography:

These are exciting times at the shop with afternoon tea coming soon .

The idea is to sell the tea via our own online shop www.terryscafe.co.uk and our forthcoming online tea shop . where we shall share recipes used for afternoon tea and to keep our loyal customers informed of our new products and ideas .

name: Tito’s
owner_biography:
Maria Zahouani is the owner and founder of La Fonda de Maria. She has a very strong passion for Latin American Cuisine - Peruvian & Colombian Cuisine in particular. However this isn't her first venture - She has a great history & her Passion for Food & hospitality has put her her amongst the top Restauranteurs in London. 

Mari established Tito's Peruvian Restaurant (London Bridge) in 2001 which was one of London's very first Peruvian Restaurants. It continues to be one of London's hot spots for an Authentic Peruvian Culinary Experience. There she transformed a small Restaurant into what is now widely regarded as London's Top Peruvian Restaurant.

La Fonda de Maria Bar & Restaurant is her latest venture where she incorporates exciting flavoursome dishes from all over Latin America in her Menu including dishes from Colombia, Argentina, Peru & the Dominican Republic. Her Travel in these Countries intrigued her to combine all these exciting flavours in one Menu.

name: José
owner_biography: José Pizarro has lived in the UK for 16 years and in that time has worked at some of London's most prestigious Spanish restaurants including Eyre Brothers, Brindisa and Gaudi. In May 2011 he opened his first solo venture to great critical acclaim - José - his proudest moment yet. Later that year he opened Pizarro, a few yards away from José. 2015 saw him open his third restaurant, José Pizarro at the newly developed Broadgate Circle in the heart of the City of London. He describes this restaurant as the coming together of his twenty years of cooking.

name: Swan
address:
Swan Shakespeare's Globe
21 New Globe Walk
Bankside SE1 9DT
owner_biography:
Executive Chef: David Johnson.

"I was about 14 when I decided I wanted to be a chef. It was just a decision I made by myself. There had never been any chefs in the family and my mother is a terrible cook, so I don't have any whimsical stories about standing next to her as a child and making tarte tatin.

My first kitchen job was in a café back in Solihull where I'm from. I think I was about 15 and I have kept one of the wage slips back, which I have at home. I was paid £2.50 an hour.

I worked in Birmingham until I was 20 and then came down to London where I have been about 13 years now. 

I was at the Albion in Islington and one of my friends knew one of the owners here at the Swan, he put me forward for the Head Chef job a couple of years ago. 

As Executive Chef I don't have a typical day or set routine. My days seem to involve running up and down flights of stairs, finding out what is going on and putting out fires here and there.

name: Granger & Co
owner_biography:
Bill Granger is a self-taught cook whose easygoing and joyful approach to cooking is an essential element in his enduring popularity.

Born in Melbourne into a family of butchers and bakers, Bill moved to Sydney when he was nineteen. As an art student with a passion for food, he worked part-time as a waiter and gradually his focus shifted from the easel to the kitchen. In 1993, at just 22 years old, he opened the original bills in the Sydney suburb of Darlinghurst, followed by another in Surry Hills in 1996 and then Woollahra in 2005. All have become firm favourites with both locals and tourists alike.

Bill opened his first international bills in Shichirigahama, Kamakura in March 2008. He then launched in Yokohama's Red Brick Warehouse in March 2010 and in Odaiba, Tokyo in July 2011. In April 2012 he brought his laid back dining concept to the fashion and culture hub of Omotesando, Tokyo. Bill's first London restaurant, Granger & Co, opened in Notting Hill in November 2011.

name: Emilia’s Crafted Pasta
address:
Unit C3 Ivory House
St Katharine Docks
London E1W 1AT
owner_biography:
I'm Andrew, the founder of Emilia's. I've loved eating pasta since I was a young boy, born of the millennial generation for whom pasta was an everyday item. From these humble beginnings started an obsession with this fascinating Italian staple.

Whilst studying maths at university I started travelling around Italy and learning more about the craft behind pasta - you don't see potatoes, rice or bread in the multitude of fun shapes you'd find pasta. I came to really appreciate the craft behind involved in creating this delicious and aesthetically pleasing food. No two pasta makers create the exact same pasta hence why it is considered a craft. I also became fascinated by the science behind the pairing of sauces with their shapes and the geometry behind the shapes.

Being the birthplace of fresh pasta, it was only natural that I focused my travels on the Emilia Romagna region, where I found the best restaurants to be local trattorias serving modest, yet delicious.....continued on website
